what is react:- 

React is a JS library, used to build user interfaces, especially single-page application (SPAs); 

why react exists:- 

traditional JS, manually update DOM, messy event handling hard to scale. 

1) UI is broken into componenents. 
2) UI updtes automatically when data changes. 
3) much easier to reason abou complex apps. 


History of react:- 

origin:- 

2011:- created at facbook by jordan walke 
2012:- used interanlly in facebook news feed. 
2013:- open-sourced at JSConf US/ 
-> JSX(HTMl in JS) was intially coontroversial. 

2014:- used in instagram.com 
2015:- react native announced (react to mobile); 
2016:- create react app lauched for boostrapping react apps. 


2019:- jooks introduced in react 16.8, revolutionaizing state management in functional componenets. 
today:- react powers facbook, instagram, netflix, airbnb, and more. 
it's also the core of Next.js, the most popular full stack react fraework. 


Virtual DOM:- 

1) lightweight JS object representing the UI; 
2) sotreed in mempry is JS objects. 
3) very fast to update. 
4) used with react (react.createElement of JSX).
5) what is it, a virtual copy of teh real DOM kept in memeory. 

eg:

{
    type:'h1', 
    props:{
        chidlrent:"hello World"
    }
}



summary

featured           V-DOM         R-DOM

speed              fast           slow 

storage            in memeory     browser

update            smart diffing  full re0render

manupulation       react logic     browser API 







